title: Push-Up
description: The push-up is a classic bodyweight exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps.
steps: Start in a plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor
Push yourself back up to the starting position
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions

title: Pull-Up
description: The pull-up is a challenging upper body exercise that primarily targets the back and biceps.
steps: Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart
Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar
Lower yourself back down with control
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions

title: Bodyweight Squat
description: The bodyweight squat is a fundamental lower body exercise that targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes.
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart
Lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back
Keep your chest up and back straight
Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground
Push through your heels to return to the starting position

title: Parallel Bar Dips
description: Dips are an effective upper body exercise that targets the chest, triceps, and shoulders.
steps: Grip parallel bars with your palms facing inward
Straighten your arms to support your body weight
Lower your body by bending your elbows until they reach a 90-degree angle
Push yourself back up to the starting position
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions

title: Plank
description: The plank is a core strengthening exercise that also engages the shoulders, arms, and glutes.
steps: Start in a push-up position, then bend your elbows and rest your weight on your forearms
Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels
Engage your core and hold the position
Hold for the desired amount of time

title: Muscle-Up
description: The muscle-up is an advanced calisthenics exercise that combines a pull-up with a dip in one fluid motion.
steps: Hang from a pull-up bar with a false grip (wrists over the bar)
Perform an explosive pull-up to bring your chest to the bar
As you reach the top of the pull-up, lean forward and push your body up and over the bar
Straighten your arms to finish in a dip position above the bar
Lower yourself back down with control

title: Handstand
description: The handstand is an advanced bodyweight skill that builds shoulder strength, balance, and body awareness.
steps: Start in a downward dog position
Kick one leg up, followed by the other
Maintain a straight body line with engaged core
Hold the position, focusing on balance
Practice against a wall for support if needed

title: L-Sit
description: The L-sit is a challenging static hold that primarily targets the core and hip flexors.
steps: Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you
Place your hands on the ground beside your hips
Press down through your hands to lift your body off the ground
Keep your legs straight and parallel to the ground
Hold the position for the desired amount of time
